<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/824> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #824" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.38.1. See Degrassi 108, 415." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/823> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #823" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "If Fabius is the active cavalry officer described in battle under the Dictator (Liv. 8.38.14ff.) he can hardly be the aged Consul of 354, who could very well have fulfilled the peaceful functions attributed by other sources (see above) to the Dictator and his staff." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/772> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #772" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Led a colony to Cales (Liv. 8.16.13-14; cf. Vell. 1.14.3). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/743> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #743" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.3.5. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 49, no. 49." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/683> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #683" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to hold elections (Liv. 7.22.10-11; Degrassi 105, 404f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/682> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #682" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the names of Fabius and Servilius, see Act. Tr. on 360 and Fast. Cap. on 365. Cf. Val. Max. 2.7.8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/665> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #665" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.18.10, both patricians; 8.33.4; Nepos, fr. 6, Peter (2.26); Diod. 16.40.1; Chr. 354 (Ambusto III et Capitolino); Cassiod.; Degrassi 105, 404f. They reduced Tibur to surrender and punished Tarquinii, arranged an armistice with Praeneste, and a treaty with the Samnites (Liv. 7.19.2-4; Diod. 16.45.8). Fabius celebrated a triumph over Tibur (Liv. 7.19.2; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; cf. FGrH 2 B. 1153, no. 255). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/664> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #664" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Fabius' name, see Act. Tr.; on that of Quinctius, Fast. Cap. on 361; and on that of Popillius, Act. Tr. on 350." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/663> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #663" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "After long delay two patrician Consuls were elected (Liv. 7.17.10-12, and 18.1). Servilius and M. Fabius were appointed twice (Liv.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/658> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #658" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.17.1, both iterum; Diod. 16.32.1; Chr. 354 (Ambusto II et Lenas II), so also Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; see Degrassi 105, 402f. Fabius fought against Falerii and Tarquinii, Popillius against Tibur (Liv. 7.17.2-5; cf. Diod. 16.36.4; Frontin. Str. 2.4.18). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/657> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #657" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "For the name and filiation of Fabius, see Act. Tr. on 360 and 354; on that of Popillius, see Act. Tr. 350. Diod. has {Gr} for Popillius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/639> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #639" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.11.2; Diod. 16.9.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Ambustus; P.'s name entire); Fast. Hyd. (Libone); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 105, 400f. Fabius celebrated an ovation for victories over the Hernici (Liv. 7.11.2 and 8-9; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540); while Poetelius made war on Tibur, harried Gallic forces and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 7.11.4 and 7-9; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540). On Poetelius, see Lübker, no. 2; Münzer, APF 27." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/638> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #638" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fabius' name is entire in Act. Tr. on 360 and 354. In Livy Poetelius' cognomen is Balbus, while Diod. has the name of {Gr}. In Chr. 354 the names of the Consuls of 358 have been substituted by mistake." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10069> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10069" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Tiburtibus. MRR I.124, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 61." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10068> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10068" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ovation de Herniceis. MRR I.120, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 56." .
